description._content: TITLE Eagle Hotel in Keene NH CREATOR Allen, W.P., Gardener MA SUBJECT Buildings - NH - Keene Hotels - NH - Keene DESCRIPTION Autoglyph print of the Eagle Hotel in Keene New Hampshire. Located at 108-120 Main Street. It was built by Captain Wm. Wyman in 1804 and was opened for business in 1806. It had a number of proprietors and was remodeled and named the Eagle in 1827, by Colonel Stephen Harrington. It had a number of owners and was remodeled several times. It was destroyed by fire in 1968. PUBLISHER Keene Public Library DATE DIGITAL 20071116 DATE ORIGINAL pre1886 RESOURCE TYPE photographs FORMAT image/jpg RESOURCE IDENTIFIER hsykbdg045 RIGHTS MANAGMENT No known restriction on publication.
